"{\"uid\": \"jamaicaobserver.com-2024-04-27-olympics-boss-distances-athletics-prize-money-move\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"LAUSANNE, Switzerland (AFP) - The head of the International Olympic Committee (IOC) distanced himself from a taboo-busting move from World Athletics' governing body to offer prize money to gold medallists at this year's Paris Olympics.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 235, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10, \"end\": 21, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\", \"score\": 0.998194152150306, \"rank\": 0.0011856000388670302, \"text\": \"Switzerland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\"}, {\"begin\": 46, \"end\": 83, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee (IOC)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 46, \"end\": 83, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee (IOC)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 133, \"end\": 148, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999802185, \"rank\": 1.9829977495774946e-11, \"text\": \"World Athletics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\"}, {\"begin\": 220, \"end\": 234, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"LAUSANNE\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 8}, {\"ngram\": \"(AFP\", \"from\": 22, \"to\": 26}, {\"ngram\": \"The head\", \"from\": 30, \"to\": 38}, {\"ngram\": \"a taboo-busting move\", \"from\": 107, \"to\": 127}, {\"ngram\": \"prize money\", \"from\": 174, \"to\": 185}, {\"ngram\": \"gold medallists\", \"from\": 189, \"to\": 204}]}, {\"sentence\": \"World Athletics president Sebastian Coe's announcement earlier this month that track and field winners at the Paris Games will receive US$50,000 (47,000 euros) has sparked mixed reactions.\", \"from\": 237, \"to\": 425, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 237, \"end\": 252, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999802185, \"rank\": 1.9829977495774946e-11, \"text\": \"World Athletics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\"}, {\"begin\": 263, \"end\": 276, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sebastian_Coe\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sebastian Coe\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sebastian_Coe\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sebastian_Coe\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"that track and field winners\", \"from\": 311, \"to\": 339}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Games\", \"from\": 343, \"to\": 358}, {\"ngram\": \"US$50,000 (47,000 euros\", \"from\": 372, \"to\": 395}, {\"ngram\": \"mixed reactions\", \"from\": 409, \"to\": 424}]}, {\"sentence\": \"No other sports federation pays prize money at the Olympics.\", \"from\": 427, \"to\": 487, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"No other sports federation\", \"from\": 427, \"to\": 453}, {\"ngram\": \"prize money\", \"from\": 459, \"to\": 470}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 474, \"to\": 486}]}, {\"sentence\": \"During an exclusive interview with AFP, IOC boss Thomas Bach made it clear that he thought international sports federations like World Athletics should be focused on reducing inequalities between countries.\", \"from\": 489, \"to\": 695, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 524, \"end\": 527, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\", \"score\": 0.9992162664108367, \"rank\": 0.0007784446305293949, \"text\": \"AFP\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\"}, {\"begin\": 529, \"end\": 532, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1215188133371517e-23, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 538, \"end\": 549, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Thomas Bach\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\"}, {\"begin\": 618, \"end\": 633, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999802185, \"rank\": 1.9829977495774946e-11, \"text\": \"World Athletics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an exclusive interview\", \"from\": 496, \"to\": 518}, {\"ngram\": \"international sports federations\", \"from\": 580, \"to\": 612}, {\"ngram\": \"inequalities\", \"from\": 664, \"to\": 676}, {\"ngram\": \"countries\", \"from\": 685, \"to\": 694}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The international federations have to treat all their member federations and their athletes on an equal basis and to try to balance this gap between the privileged and the less or under-privileged,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 697, \"to\": 905, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The international federations\", \"from\": 698, \"to\": 727}, {\"ngram\": \"all their member federations\", \"from\": 742, \"to\": 770}, {\"ngram\": \"their athletes\", \"from\": 775, \"to\": 789}, {\"ngram\": \"an equal basis\", \"from\": 793, \"to\": 807}, {\"ngram\": \"this gap\", \"from\": 830, \"to\": 838}]}, {\"sentence\": \"National Olympic committees rather than international federations were free to motivate their athletes with prize money, he said, noting that he received money from the German committee for his fencing gold medal in 1976.\", \"from\": 907, \"to\": 1128, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 907, \"end\": 934, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 0.9999999194778898, \"rank\": 8.052202707777714e-08, \"text\": \"National Olympic committees\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 1076, \"end\": 1082, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/German_language\", \"score\": 0.9814149671253342, \"rank\": 0.011589217898260897, \"text\": \"German\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/German_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/German_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"international federations\", \"from\": 947, \"to\": 972}, {\"ngram\": \"their athletes\", \"from\": 995, \"to\": 1009}, {\"ngram\": \"prize money\", \"from\": 1015, \"to\": 1026}, {\"ngram\": \"money\", \"from\": 1061, \"to\": 1066}, {\"ngram\": \"his fencing gold medal\", \"from\": 1097, \"to\": 1119}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Each pillar of the Olympic movement has its role to play,\\\" he said, adding: \\\"It's very clear what the responsibility of an international federation is and what the responsibility of a national Olympic committee is.\\\"\", \"from\": 1130, \"to\": 1346, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Each pillar\", \"from\": 1131, \"to\": 1142}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic movement\", \"from\": 1146, \"to\": 1166}, {\"ngram\": \"its role\", \"from\": 1171, \"to\": 1179}, {\"ngram\": \"the responsibility\", \"from\": 1229, \"to\": 1247}, {\"ngram\": \"an international federation\", \"from\": 1251, \"to\": 1278}, {\"ngram\": \"the responsibility\", \"from\": 1291, \"to\": 1309}, {\"ngram\": \"a national Olympic committee\", \"from\": 1313, \"to\": 1341}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Coe's move was welcomed by some leading athletes, but has sparked a backlash from bosses of other sports amid concerns it will further entrench the advantages of rich countries.\", \"from\": 1348, \"to\": 1525, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Coe's move\", \"from\": 1348, \"to\": 1358}, {\"ngram\": \"some leading athletes\", \"from\": 1375, \"to\": 1396}, {\"ngram\": \"a backlash\", \"from\": 1414, \"to\": 1424}, {\"ngram\": \"bosses\", \"from\": 1430, \"to\": 1436}, {\"ngram\": \"other sports\", \"from\": 1440, \"to\": 1452}, {\"ngram\": \"concerns\", \"from\": 1458, \"to\": 1466}, {\"ngram\": \"the advantages\", \"from\": 1492, \"to\": 1506}, {\"ngram\": \"rich countries\", \"from\": 1510, \"to\": 1524}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Association of Summer Olympic International Federations (ASOIF) said it \\\"undermined the values of Olympism\\\" and the Association of National Olympic Committees of Africa called the move \\\"repugnant to the fundamental principles of the Olympic Movement\\\".\", \"from\": 1527, \"to\": 1782, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1764, \"end\": 1780, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Inte